        section#descricao.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center
                    h1 Marketing and E-Commerce Management

                .decptext.text-start        
                    p.lead.fw-bold The diploma of higher professional technician in Marketing Management and Electronic Commerce is awarded to students who demonstrate, in this area:
                    p.lead a) possess knowledge and comprehension skills; 
                    p.lead b) know how to apply, in professional contexts, the knowledge and comprehension skills acquired;
                    p.lead c) have the ability to identify and use information to respond to well-defined concrete and abstract problems;
                    p.lead d) possess skills that enable them to communicate about their understanding of issues, skills and activities with their peers, supervisors and clients;
                    p.lead e) Possess learning skills that allow them to pursue studies with some autonomy.

        section#perfil.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Profile of the study program

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead Collaborate, autonomously or under supervision, in the commercial or marketing department, using organization, argumentation, negotiation and sales techniques, relying on tools based on information and communication technologies, promoting the prospection and acquisition of new customers and ensuring the satisfaction and loyalty of current customers


        section#diplomados.mt-5
            .container
                .decptext.text-center 
                    h2 Occupational profile of graduates

                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead.fw-bold The Higher Technical Professional Course in Marketing and Electronic Commerce Management is part of the Marketing and Advertising training area, and its graduates are prepared to perform technical functions, within the scope of the study program profile:
                    p.lead - Manage the commercial or sales area using the appropriate communication, sales and distribution channels.
                    p.lead - Participate in the marketing management of the organization.
                    p.lead - Study the organization's products and/or services, characterize the type of customers and gather information about the competition and the market in general.
                    p.lead - Define product strategies based on the reading and perception of customer needs, acting as a link between the company and the customer.
                    p.lead - Streamline sales promotion and customer follow-up.
                    p.lead - Manage products, teams and points of sale.
                    p.lead - Supervise the application of omni-channel service and sales techniques.
                    p.lead - Plan and control stocks.
                    p.lead - Monitor satisfaction levels, manage and promote customer loyalty.
                    p.lead - Design and coordinate the after-sales service, acting in the solidification of the partnership relationship with the customer.
                    p.lead - Manage information by effectively integrating the different computer applications to support the activity.

